OL,6,FPowell would visit his grandmother,
OL,7,Fwhom he called Oma, once a week, and
OL,8,Fcalled her the "one constant in my
OL,9,Flife that I could count on", in an
OL,10,Fapology letter he wrote to Portsmouth
OL,11,FCrown Court.
OL,13,FThe court heard he was in debt, owed
OL,14,Fmoney to his landlord and "snapped".
OL,16,FJudge Michael Bowes KC said: "Emma
OL,17,FFinch, your grandmother, showed you
OL,18,Fgreat kindness and gave you a great
OL,19,Fdeal of money during her life.
