OL,6,F"The word sorry does not even begin to
OL,7,Fcover how I feel for the unforgivable,
OL,8,Ftruly horrible crime I committed," the
OL,9,Fdefendant wrote.
OL,11,F"Oma was the one constant in my life
OL,12,Fthat I could count on. She was there
OL,13,Ffor me no matter how good or bad I
OL,14,Fbehaved as a child. She was a
OL,15,Fwonderful, caring, loving, happy woman
OL,16,Fwho when entering a room suddenly
OL,17,Fbrightened it up tenfold.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@bO]sD@AOU
